This paper is about applying quantization techniques to fully convolutional networks (FCNs) for accurate biomedical image segmentation. The paper focuses on reducing overfitting in FCNs for better accuracy, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep neural networks (DNNs) also suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions the reduction of memory usage, which suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
